content:
Preview Your Messaging for Web Setup

This article applies to: Messaging for Web channels.

To ensure that Messaging for Web is set up properly, follow these steps:

Open the Service Console app and go online as the agent assigned to the messaging button.
From Setup, enter Embedded Service Deployments, select Embedded Service Deployments, and click View.
Click Test Messaging on the Test Messaging card.
Click to open the messaging conversation window and initiate a messaging session as a customer.
In the console tab, verify that you received a conversation request. Accept the request and try sending a message.

If set up properly, you're able to request a chat and complete the form as the customer. Also, the pre-chat information is sent to the agent before the conversation begins.

TIP: To turn on and customize Messaging for In-App and Web in your sandbox, ensure that you have the correct edition.
title: Service Cloud Messaging Setup
